	<description>
	Lost For Swords is a Roguelike Deckbuilder, where the cards in your deck shape the rooms you're exploring. Make your way up the tower, equip weapons and armor, cast spells and scrolls, activate auras, collect loot and defeat monsters in tactical turn-based combat.
	</description>
	
	<history>
	I've always wanted to create a digital card game, one that has a very low input complexity (no card dragging, no "hand", no menus or inventories), and yet offers strategic and deep gameplay. Lost For Swords is my best attempt at such a game!
	</history>

	<features>
		<feature>Deck Building and Playstyles: build and refine your deck as you fight your way up the towers. Choose wisely and craft the best deck from 100+ available cards. Play offensive or defensive, sneaky or powerful, deliberate or reckless. You decide!</feature>
		<feature>Simple UI, Complex Strategy: every single one of your actions is a simple click. No inventory management, no menus, no card dragging, no busywork. Just pure turn based strategy and tactics!</feature>
		<feature>Roguelike Runs: choose a hero and ascend the floors of a tower that is ever-changing. No two runs are the same. How far can you make it?</feature>
	</features>
	
